   <name>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Port of San Vicente is located 520 km to the south of Santiago and 18 km from Concepcion, the capital of region VIII.  The area under the concession comprises three berths (603 meter total length) which are designed for all vessel types, with a maximum draft of 12.2 meters.  The port covers a total area of 40 hectares of which 14 hectares are hilly or unsurfaced.  This includes 2,000 ground slots for container stacking and 3.5 hectares of covered storage space in large high-sided warehouses.</narrative>
   </name>
